video:video.video:title: Former CNN host Don Lemon arrives in court for hearing
video:video.video:description: Don Lemon is accused in a protest at a Minnesota church where an Immigration and Customs Enforcement official is a pastor. (AP Video: Mark Vancleave)

video:video.video:title: Krewe of Bosom Buddies keep Mardi Gras celebrations rolling in New Orleans
video:video.video:description: The Krewe of Bosom Buddies celebrate Carnival by handing out decorated bras as they walk through the French Quarter's narrow streets.

video:video.video:title: IOC President explains decision to not allow Ukrainian athlete Heraskevych to compete
video:video.video:description: Ukrainian skeleton racer Vladyslav Heraskevych was excluded from the Olympics after refusing to give up his plan to race in a helmet commemorating athletes who have been killed since Russia invaded his country.

video:video.video:title: Inflation measure falls to nearly five-year low as gas prices fall and housing costs cool
video:video.video:description: A key measure of inflation fell to nearly a five-year low last month as apartment rental price growth slowed and gas prices fell, offering some relief to Americans still grappling with the sharp increase in costs of the past five years.

video:video.video:title: What to know about the Homeland Security shutdown
video:video.video:description: What to know about the partial government shutdown impacting agencies under the Department of Homeland Security as lawmakers debate new restrictions on President Donald Trump’s immigration enforcement agenda.

video:video.video:title: Minneapolis mayor says federal immigration operation cost the city's economy $203 million
video:video.video:description: Minneapolis Mayor Jacob Frey said the damage from the Trump administration's immigration enforcement surge in the city would be lasting and called on the federal government to help pay the costs.

video:video.video:title: Chinese fine dining slices through American takeout stereotypes
video:video.video:description: Upscale Chinese American restaurants from San Francisco to New York are drawing buzz beyond takeout staples with refined tasting menus, while pressing diners to see their cuisine as worthy of fine dining prices.

video:video.video:title: Yappy Valentine's Day: loved up gifts for your pets
video:video.video:description: British pet owners are celebrating Valentine's Day alongside their animals, with retailers reporting a dramatic surge in purchases of treats, toys and grooming packages.

video:video.video:title: Supporters greet Nepal's former king Gyanendra Shah at Kathmandu airport
video:video.video:description: Thousands of supporters of Nepal's former king gathered outside Kathmandu airport Friday to greet him and demand the restoration of the abolished monarchy in the Himalayan nation.

video:video.video:title: Nevada sex workers push for historic fight to unionize
video:video.video:description: Nevada is the only state where people can legally purchase sex, and now sex workers at one of the state’s oldest brothels are fighting to become the nation’s first to be unionized.

video:video.video:title: Palestinians try to salvage Gaza's Great Omari Mosque from the ruins of Israeli strikes
video:video.video:description: Ismail Al-Mishal was one of many residents of Gaza City who used to visit and pray at the Great Omari Mosque.

video:video.video:title: Boat gets caught in ocean waves and capsizes off Santa Cruz coast
video:video.video:description: Speeding past surfers and large waves, the boat was engulfed by the water and is knocked on its side and capsizes.

video:video.video:title: Supriya Ganesh is enjoying the perks of 'The Pitt'
video:video.video:description: From attending a Michael Kors fashion show to working on the hit series "The Pitt" with Noah Wyle, Supriya Ganesh loves the opportunities the series brings. (Feb. 13)

video:video.video:title: Prime Minister Carney and Canada's main opposition leader hold hands during school shooting vigil
video:video.video:description: Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney and the country’s opposition leaders paid tribute to the victims of one of the worst mass shootings in the country’s history at a vigil in the devastated northern British Columbia town.

video:video.video:title: Prisoners released from detention centre in Caracas
video:video.video:description: Prisoners released from detention centre in Caracas
